NAME
       _printf - custom implementation of the printf function

SYNOPSIS
       #include "main.h"

       int _printf(const char *format, ...);

DESCRIPTION
       The _printf function writes formatted output to the standard output.

       Supported format specifiers:

       %c      Print a single character.
       %s      Print a null-terminated string. If NULL, "(null)" is printed.
       %%      Print a literal percent sign.
       %d      Print a decimal integer.
       %i      Print an integer (base 10).

       If an unknown specifier is encountered, the percent sign and
       the specifier character are printed as-is.

RETURN VALUE
       Returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).
       Returns -1 if format is NULL.

